Hi @Ed, thanks for the example.

There are two methods to find pwmX file,

1. first method (original one), assume pwmX and fanX_input are locate at same folder.
```
auto path = directory / ("pwm" + std::to_string(pwm + 1));
if (fs::exists(path, ec)) {
    if (!ec) {
        pwmPath = path;
        return true;
    }
}
```

2. second method (device node declare with pwm-fan)
With pwm-fan driver, pwmX and fanX_input are no longer locate at same folder.
The pwmX file are separate into each pwn-fanX folder, it means we needs configured pwm index in EM to find corresponding pwn-fanX folder and pwmX file, and `findPwmfanPath()` is created for this purpose.


